&lt;h3 id="_ingredients"&gt;Ingredients&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="sectionbody"&gt;
&lt;table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch"&gt;
&lt;colgroup&gt;
&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;
&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;
&lt;/colgroup&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2 pounds cross-rib roast&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2 tablespoons minced garlic&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2 teaspoons dried thyme&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 teaspoon dried rosemary&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 tablespoon salt&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 teaspoon pepper&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 tablespoon olive oil&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="sect1"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="_directions"&gt;Directions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="sectionbody"&gt;
&lt;div class="olist arabic"&gt;
&lt;ol class="arabic"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brush roast with balsamic vinegar.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Make a paste with remaining ingredients and apply to meat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Roast meat at 450 for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350 and cook for 40 to 60 minutes, or until internal temperature reaches 125.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remove from oven; cover loosely with foil and let stand 15 to 25 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="paragraph"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note: This results in a well done roast. For a more rare roast, cook until an internal temp of 120.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
